The US election has been front and centre of news headlines for weeks

But there‚Äôs another big story in America - the alarming rise of Covid-19

[Thread] üëá

https://t.co/A8exufaE8c https://t.co/aw5sSrvcO9

name: BBCWorld
text:
With more than 11m confirmed cases, the US has the highest number of infections in the world and cases are rising

It‚Äôs not just down to increased testing - tests carried out in the US were up by 12.5% week on week, while cases increased by more than 40%

https://t.co/A8exufaE8c https://t.co/GrbbZtfJcy

name: BBCWorld
text:
Roughly the same number of people across the US were in hospital with Covid during the first and second waves of the outbreak

But this third wave is even greater - by more than 70,000 at the moment 

https://t.co/A8exufaE8c https://t.co/eP1oXMAPb0

name: BBCWorld
text:
More than 1,000 people are now dying from Covid every day in America

The death toll is currently at 250,000 - the highest in the world

The worry is that statistics on deaths lag behind cases and hospitalisations - so things could look worse, shortly 

https://t.co/A8exufaE8c https://t.co/WhOc4ik5Xo

name: BBCWorld
text:
This wave is hitting every US region
